- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper focuses on social media platform Twitter and its impact on communication. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with extracting geographic entities from user descriptions metadata. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a novel grid-based approach for location inference. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper employs supervised Multinomial Naive Bayes for classification.
